# cPanel Logs and Stats

## Website Related Logs

cPanel comes with different tools that provide customers a detailed statistics. Its all under in cPanel Logs section.

You can view your account bandwidth, webstats like awstats and webalizer, Apache error log, Raw access logs etc.

- To view them login to cpanel account of your websites
- Then scroll down and find the Logs section

```diagram

```

- Click on the Tool icon to get the details of that.

## Account Information/Statistics

On the left cPanel menu there is a Statistics section named Stats. You can get the details of your account and the current usage of your account resources.

## How to View Service Status from cPanel

You can view the service status from cPanel.

- Login to your cPanel account
- On the bottom of left cPanel menu you will get a link to view Service Status. Click on link Click to View

```diagram

```

- It will open a window with Server Status information. 
  - Status GREEN: Mean service is UP
  - Status RED: Mean Service is DOWN
  
  ```diagram

```
